{
  "texts": [
    "These FFN layers, which follow the attention layers in the Transformer architecture (Vaswani et al., 2023), primarily serve to maintain the isotropy of token embeddings (Sonkar and Baraniuk, 2023).",
    "As the FFN layers of TinyLlama comprise 0.76 billion parameters, integrating one expert model adds 0.76 billion, rather than the entire 1.1 billion parameters.",
    "As the FFN layers are frozen in MoFE, only the parameters located before the FFN blocks, which include the embeddings and self-attention layers provided by the base model, and the router, are updated.",
    "The router, or gate, includes a linear layer that determines which FFN block to activate for each token at every time step.",
    "This research uses a common gating method that leverages hidden state representations of positive and negative prompts, assigned during model merging."
  ]
}